listItems.title: The Larry Sanders Show: Season 4
listItems.description: Comic Garry Shandling draws upon his own talk show experiences to create the character of Larry Sanders, a paranoid, insecure host of a late night talk show.  Larry, along with his obsequious TV sidekick Hank Kingsley and his fiercely protective producer Artie, allows Garry Shandling and his talented writers to look behind the scenes and to show us a convincing slice of behind the camera life.

listItems.description: Oprah Winfrey's interview with Prince Harry and Meghan, the Duke and Duchess of Sussex includes discussions of their decision to move to the U.S. and their future.

listItems.title: 2 Dope Queens: Season 1
listItems.description: The comedy podcast with Jessica Williams and Phoebe Robinson becomes a series of TV specials with guest appearances from Uzo Aduba, Tituss Burgess, Sarah Jessica Parker, and Jon Stewart.

listItems.title: Boston Med: Season 1
listItems.description: After "Hopkins 24/7"  and "Hopkins," ABC follows up with a look at the doctors, nurses, and patients at Massachusetts General Hospital, Brigham and Women's Hospital, and Children's Hospital Boston.

listItems.title: Wu-Tang Clan: Of Mics and Men: Season 1
listItems.description: The four-part documentary from Sacha Jenkins takes a look at the hip-hop group's formation and long career with never-before-seen archival footage and interviews with all living nine members.

listItems.title: Full Frontal with Samantha Bee: Season 1
listItems.description: The former Daily Show correspondent hosts her own late-night satirical talk show on TBS.

listItems.title: Random Acts Of Flyness: Season 1
listItems.description: The late-night show from Terence Nance will feature a variety of vignettes that include "vérité documentary, musical performances, surrealist melodrama and humorous animation" to explore American culture through a range of topics such as death, history, patriarchy, police brutality, romance, and white supremacy.

listItems.title: McCartney 3,2,1: Season 1
listItems.description: The six-part documentary series features Paul McCartney talking with producer Rick Rubin about music as well as his career with the Beatles, Wings and as a solo artist.

listItems.title: Surviving R. Kelly: Season 1
listItems.description: The six-part documentary series features interviews with the young women who allege to have suffered sexual, mental, and physical abuse from the R&B singer as well as music industry professionals, journalists, former employees and family members of Kelly.

listItems.title: Sherman's Showcase Black History Month Spectacular
listItems.description: The one-hour special features Sherman McDaniels (Bashir Salahuddin) celebrating Black History Month in June.

listItems.title: Maron: Season 4
listItems.description: Andy Dick, Adam Goldberg, Patton Oswalt, Ron Perlman, and Amy Smart are some of the guests on the fourth season of the comedy about the fictionalized version of comedian/podcaster Marc Maron.

listItems.title: Showbiz Kids
listItems.description: Alex Winter's documentary about child actors features interviews with former child stars including Cameron Boyce, Todd Bridges, Diana Serra Cary, Milla Jovovich, Jada Pinkett Smith, Henry Thomas, Wil Wheaton, Mara Wilson, and Evan Rachel Wood.

listItems.title: Five Came Back: Season 1
listItems.description: Narrated by Meryl Streep, the three-part documentary based on Mark Harris's 2014 book about Frank Capra, John Ford, John Huston, George Stevens and William Wyler's experiences in and after World War II features interviews from Steven Spielberg, Francis Ford Coppola, Guillermo del Toro, Paul Greengrass and Lawrence Kasdan.

listItems.title: Nothing Left Unsaid: Gloria Vanderbilt & Anderson Cooper
listItems.description: Gloria Vanderbilt and her son, CNN's Anderson Cooper, discuss her life and career in this Liz Garbus documentary.

listItems.title: Desus & Mero: Season 1
listItems.description: Desus Nice and The Kid Mero move their late-night talk show from Viceland to Showtime.

listItems.title: Becoming Mike Nichols: Season 1
listItems.description: The documentary about director Mike Nichols features edited portions of two discussion from 2014 between Nichols and theater director Jack O'Brien.

listItems.title: Patriot Act with Hasan Minhaj: Season 1
listItems.description: The Daily Show correspondent is the latest alumni to host his own weekly comedy series.

listItems.title: Hopkins: Season 1
listItems.description: ABC returns to expand on its "Hopkins 24/7" documentary with a six-episode series about the lives of the doctors and the people they treat at the prestigious Johns Hopkins Hospital.

listItems.title: The Rundown With Robin Thede: Season 1
listItems.description: Former head writer for The Nightly Show With Larry Wilmore, Robin Thede joins the late-night talk show line-up with her weekly 30-minutes series.

listItems.title: On Death Row: Season 1
listItems.description: Werner Herzog interviews five inmates on death row about the crimes they committed and life in jail.

listItems.title: Watergate: Season 1
listItems.description: The three-part documentary from Charles Ferguson seeks to give a comprehensive look at the conspiracy that led to the downfall of Richard Nixon features interviews with Daniel Ellsberg, Elizabeth Holtzman, the late Senator John McCain, Dan Rather, William Ruckelshaus, and Lesley Stahl.

listItems.title: Last Week Tonight with John Oliver: Season 1

listItems.title: Spectacle: Elvis Costello With...: Season 1
listItems.description: The Sundance channel brings Costello to TV with a new talk show featuring mainly musicians as guests.

listItems.title: Talking Funny
listItems.description: Louis C.K., Ricky Gervais, Chris Rock, and Jerry Seinfeld discuss the different aspects of being a successful comedian.

listItems.title: Lewis Black's Root of All Evil: Season 1
listItems.description: Comedians debate pop culture subjects with The Daily Show's Lewis Black as the judge.

listItems.title: The Writers' Room: Season 1
listItems.description: Jim Rash talks with the creative teams behind Breaking Bad, Parks & Recreation, Dexter, New Girl, Game of Thrones, and American Horror Stories.

listItems.title: Demi Lovato: Dancing with the Devil: Season 1
listItems.description: The four-part documentary series directed by Michael D. Ratner features discussions of the pop singer's personal and professional life including what led to her near-fatal drug overdose in 2018 and her ensuing recovery.

listItems.title: Late Show with Stephen Colbert: Season 1
listItems.description: Stephen Colbert moves from his satirical late night show, "The Colbert Report" to take over David Letterman's seat at the long-running CBS late night talk show.

listItems.title: The Not Too Late Show with Elmo: Season 1
listItems.description: Elmo hosts a talk show that includes guests from Sesame Street and celebrities such as Jimmy Fallon, The Jonas Brothers, Lil Nas X, Blake Lively, John Mullaney, and John Oliver

listItems.title: Maron: Season 1
listItems.description: Marc Maron stars as a fictionalized version of himself in this new sitcom.

listItems.title: My Next Guest Needs No Introduction With David Letterman: Season 1
listItems.description: David Letterman returns to the talk show world with a monthly series and the six-episode first season will include President Barack Obama, George Clooney, Tina Fey, Jay-Z, Malala Yousafzai, and Howard Stern.

listItems.title: Maron: Season 2
listItems.description: Michael Ian Black, David Cross, Chris Hardwick, Johnny Knoxville, Conan O’Brien, Andy Richter, Ray Romano, and Sarah Silverman are some of the guests on the second season of the comedy about the fictionalized version of comedian/podcaster Marc Maron.

listItems.title: Sit Down Comedy with David Steinberg: Season 1
listItems.description: This six-episode series finds the writer/comedian/director in one-on-one conversations with fellow comedians Mike Myers, Larry David, Martin Short, Bob Newhart, Jon Lovitz and George Lopez.

listItems.title: Ziwe: Season 1
listItems.description: The late-night variety show from writer/comedian Ziwe will feature interviews, unscripted segments and sketches.

listItems.title: It Gets Better
listItems.description: Profiles of three LGBT teenagers are the focus of this MTV special based on the The It Gets Better Project begun by Dan Savage and his partner, Terry Miller.

listItems.title: The Nightly Show with Larry Wilmore: Season 1
listItems.description: With Stephen Colbert moving to CBS, Larry Wilmore takes over the time slot with his own daily late night show.

listItems.title: George W. Bush: The 9/11 Interview
listItems.description: Former President George W. Bush is interviewed about his thoughts and feelings during and after the attacks on September 11th.

listItems.title: Vice: Season 1
listItems.description: Shane Smiths host the news magazine series that covers provocative stories from around the world.

listItems.title: The Late Late Show with James Corden: Season 1
listItems.description: British actor/comedian James Corden takes over The Late Late Show from  Craig Ferguson.

listItems.title: The Rosie Show : Season 1
listItems.description: Rosie O'Donnell returns to talk show television on Oprah's OWN, which airs live from Chicago.

listItems.title: State of Mind: Season 1
listItems.description: The problems patients of Ann Bellos have, are nothing compared to hers when she discovers her husband is cheating on her with their marriage counselor.

listItems.title: The Tonight Show with Conan O'Brien: Season 1
listItems.description: Conan O'Brien takes over the long-running late-night talk show from Jay Leno.

listItems.title: Da Ali G Show (US): Season 2
listItems.description: Note:  Show aired on HBO, thus content contained in this guide may not be suitable for children.The outrageous comedy/reality series stars British chameleon Sacha Baron Cohen,  who travels across America in the guise of one of three totally different characters. Cohen's primary alter-ego is Ali G., who calls himself a "hip-hop journalist", but who's really a white rapper-wannabe. When Cohen isn't putting Ali G and his "guests" in unusual and often delightfully uncomfortable situations, he's shedding his yellow gangsta track suit attire and slipping into two other memorable characters: Borat, an impossibly naive TV reporter from Kazakhstan, and Bruno, a gay Austrian fashionista. The series aired under the name 'Ali G in da USAiii' in the UK, on channel 4, were the original show aired.

listItems.title: Would You Rather...? with Graham Norton: Season 1
listItems.description: Talk show host Graham Norton presents BBC America's first original programming. The panel game show features celebrities who must choose from one of the options provided in the questions.

listItems.title: Star Trek: Enterprise: Season 1
listItems.description: "It's Good to be Home."Star Trek: Enterprise is the latest entry in the Star Trek saga and takes place during the mid-22nd century. Under the command of Captain Jonathan Archer, the crew of the first warp five starship (the Enterprise NX-01) begin to explore the galaxy. As their mission progresses, the crew encounter familiar races like the Klingons and Andorians as well as some new ones.Starting in the first episode, the Enterprise crew discover their time has become a front in the mysterious Temporal Cold War. They sometimes find themselves up against the Suliban, an aggressive race that is apart of a faction of the war and given orders by an unknown being from the future. In the second season finale, things take a deadly turn when an alien race named the Xindi attack Earth. With the Xindi preparing another attack and humanity facing destruction, the Enterprise crew have only one option. The third season sees the crew searching the mysterious Delphic Expanse for the Xindi and trying to stop them before their next attack. The fourth season has the crew back home and opening up brand new adventures, one with special guest Brent Spiner. As of season four, T'Pol has officially left the Vulcan High Command and joined Starfleet Command, she has been promoted to Commander.The theme tune for Enterprise is titled "Faith of the Heart", performed by Russell Watson and written by Diane Warren.

listItems.title: Conan (2010): Season 9
listItems.description: For its ninth season, Conan becomes a half-hour long talk show airing Monday through Thursday.

listItems.title: The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon: Season 1
listItems.description: Jimmy Fallon takes over hosting duties from Jay Leno as the legendary nightly talk show moves to New York City.

listItems.title: The Colbert Report: Season 1
listItems.description: This Daily Show spinoff elevates bear-phobic Stephen Colbert to the anchor seat, where he takes on cable news hosts such as Bill O'Reilly.

listItems.title: The Daily Show with Trevor Noah: Season 1
listItems.description: South African comedian Trevor Noah takes over hosting duties for Jon Stewart's satirical news/talk show.

listItems.title: Conan (2010): Season 1
listItems.description: Conan O'Brien returns to late-night television; this time on cable network TBS. Sidekick Andy Richter also returns, as Jimmy Vivino takes over Max Weinberg's spot as band leader

listItems.title: The Approval Matrix: Season 1
listItems.description: Hosted by comedian Neal Brennan, the talk show inspired by New York Magazine's Approval Matrix page, features a panel of celebrities and comedians discussing weekly news and entertainment items.

listItems.title: The New Yorker Presents: Season 1
listItems.description: The newsmagazine series produced by Alex Gibney features short films, comedy, poetry, animation, documentaries, and interviews.

listItems.title: Iconoclasts: Season 1
listItems.description: This six part original Sundance series pairs two "innovative leaders" (we call them "celebrities") each episode for an in-depth conversation. If you've ever wanted to see celebrity chef Mario Batali talking to R.E.M.'s Michael Stipe, now's your chance.

listItems.title: Bill Nye Saves the World: Season 1
listItems.description: The science talk show hosted by Bill Nye will feature experiments, demonstrations and special guests such as Steve Aoki, Rachel Bloom, Zach Braff, Donald Faison, Tim Gunn, Joel McHale, and Wil Wheaton.

listItems.title: The Presidents' Gatekeepers: Season 1
listItems.description: The two-part documentary interviews 20 former White House chiefs of staff including: James Baker, Rahm Emanuel, Leon Panetta, Donald Rumsfeld and Dick Cheney, about events during their time administration.

listItems.title: The Ricky Gervais Show: Season 1
listItems.description: Ricky Gervais returns with an animated comedy that began as a radio show, continued in his podcasts, and now exists as a cartoon with collaborators Stephen Merchant and Karl Pilington.

listItems.title: A Little Late with Lilly Singh: Season 1
listItems.description: Lilly Singh joins the fall TV season as the only women hosting a late-night talk show on network television.

listItems.title: Comedians in Cars Getting Coffee: Season 10
listItems.description: Comedian Jerry Seinfeld shares coffee and car rides with Alec Baldwin, Neal Brennan, Dana Carvey, Dave Chappelle, Ellen DeGeneres, Zach Galifinakis, Jerry Lewis (posthumously), Kate McKinnon, Hasan Minhaj, Tracy Morgan and John Mulaney, and Brian Regan as the web series moves to Netflix for its 10th season.

listItems.title: Late Night with Seth Meyers: Season 1
listItems.description: Saturday Night Live's Seth Meyers takes over Late Night with Jimmy Fallon's move over to the Tonight Show.

listItems.title: The Me You Can't See: Season 1

listItems.title: The View: Season 18

listItems.title: Who Is America?: Season 1

listItems.title: Mars: Season 1
listItems.description: Produced by Ron Howard, the hybrid miniseries features a scripted drama set in 2033 as six astronauts set out on the first mission to Mars with real documentary interviews with experts such as NASA administrator Charles Bolden, X-Prize Foundation head Peter Diamandis, Elon Musk, Neil deGrasse Tyson, and The Martian author Andy Weir.

listItems.title: The President Show: Season 1
listItems.description: The comedy series features "President Trump" (Anthony Atamanuik) hosting a late-night talk show with his vice president (Peter Grosz).

listItems.title: Rolling Stone: Stories From the Edge: Season 1
listItems.description: The two-part documentary by Alex Gibney and Blair Foster explores the impact of the magazine and the stories it covered.

listItems.title: The Chew: Season 1
listItems.description: Hosted by Mario Batali, Carla Hall, Clinton Kelly, Michael Symon and Daphne Oz, the talk show focuses not only on food, but other issues that connect to it.

listItems.title: The Opposition with Jordan Klepper: Season 1
listItems.description: The Daily Show correspondent hosts the latest satirical late night talk show for Comedy Central.

listItems.title: StarTalk: Season 1
listItems.description: Based on Neil deGrasse Tyson's podcast, the daily talk show will feature interviews about science with a variety of guests.

listItems.title: Drunk History: Season 1
listItems.description: Jack Black, Michael Cera, Dave Grohl, Winona Ryder, and Kristen Wiig are some of actors on the comedy show based on the Funny Or Die concept where historical reenactments are explained by drunk narrators.

listItems.title: The Putin Interviews: Season 1
listItems.description: Airing over four consecutive nights, Oliver Stone's four-part interview with Russian president Vladimir Putin was recorded over a two years from over a dozen conversations.

listItems.title: Daytime Divas: Season 1
listItems.description: Maxine Robinson (Vanessa Williams) created and hosts a daytime talk show with her cohosts: comedienne Mo Evans (Tichina Arnold), ex-child star Kibby Ainsley (Chloe Bridges), investigative journalist Nina Sandoval (Camille Guaty), and conservative Heather Flynn-Kellog (Fiona Gubelmann) in this drama series based on Satan's Sisters, a book by Star Jones.

listItems.title: Jon Benjamin Has A Van: Season 1
listItems.description: H. Jon Benjamin, better known as the voice behind Archer and Bob in Bob's Burgers, is an investigative reporter in this spoof of the genre.

listItems.title: Countdown with Keith Olbermann: Season 9
listItems.description: Keith Olbermann moves his weekday news show to Current TV.

listItems.title: Any Given Wednesday with Bill Simmons: Season 1
listItems.description: Former ESPN commentator Bill Simmons hosts a new weekly talk show with an emphasis on sports, but will also cover pop culture and technology for HBO.

listItems.title: Chelsea: Season 1
listItems.description: Chelsea Handler's talk show on Netflix will air three times a week (Wednesday, Thursday and Friday).

listItems.title: The Tonight Show with Jay Leno: Season 18
listItems.description: Jay Leno returns to the Tonight Show after NBC's failed experiment to have his own show on at 10:00p.

listItems.title: Late Night with Jimmy Fallon: Season 1
listItems.description: Jimmy Fallon takes over for Conan O'Brien as NBC shuffles its late night talk show roster in 2009.

listItems.title: Maya & Marty: Season 1
listItems.description: The variety show hosted by Maya Rudolph and Martin short will be aired live from Studio 6A in Rockefeller Center.

listItems.title: The Jay Leno Show : Season 1
listItems.description: Leno returns to NBC but at the 10 p.m. time slot after being pursued by other networks. The talk show will feature his popular Tonight Show segments, but expect them in the later half of the show.

listItems.title: Sundays with Alec Baldwin: Season 1
listItems.description: Each episode of Alec Baldwin's talk show features one-on-one conversations with two people in pop culture.

listItems.title: Real Time With Bill Maher: Season 1
listItems.description: Real Time with Bill Maher is an HBO panel talk show series hosted by comedian and Bill Maher.  Episodes generally feature an opening political sketch, a monologue, a panel of three celebrities and/or politicians, a guest or two live or via satellite, and a New Rules segment.

listItems.title: The Show With Vinny: Season 1
listItems.description: Celebrities come for a meal and a chat with Jersey Shore's Vinny Guadagnino at his family's house in Staten Island.

listItems.title: Norm MacDonald Has a Show: Season 1
listItems.description: The hour-long comedic talk show with the Saturday Night Live alumni and Adam Eget features interviews with Drew Barrymore, Chevy Chase, David Letterman, Jane Fonda, Michael Keaton, Lorne Michaels, Billy Joe Shaver, Judy Sheindlin, M. Night Shyamalan, and David Spade.

listItems.title: TALKSHOW with Spike Feresten: Season 1
listItems.description: The former "Seinfeld" and "Late Show with David Letterman" writer makes the move to the front of the camera for Fox's latest attempt at a late-night talk show, airing Saturday nights following "Mad TV."

listItems.title: Katie: Season 1
listItems.description: Katie Couric returns to daytime television with a new talk show with Jessica Simpson and Sheryl Crow as her first guests.

listItems.title: The Showbiz Show with David Spade: Season 1
listItems.description: "The Showbiz Show" attempts to do for entertainment news what "The Daily Show" does for news and politics. Former SNL cast member David Spade hosts the show and offers his take on the headlines from behind a desk, supplemented by taped features.

listItems.title: Sunday Night With Megyn Kelly: Season 1
listItems.description: The newsmagazine show hosted by former Fox News anchor Megyn Kelly.

listItems.title: The Talk: Season 1
listItems.description: Sara Gilbert co-hosts with Sharon Osbourne, Leah Remini, Julie Chen, Holly Robinson Peete, and Marissa Jaret Winokur in this morning talk billed as a show for mothers.

listItems.title: Megyn Kelly Today: Season 1
listItems.description: The morning talk show hosted by former Fox News anchor Megyn Kelly features celebrity interviews with news and lifestyles segments.

listItems.title: Raising McCain: Season 1
listItems.description: The series follows Meghan McCain, daughter of Arizona Senator John McCain, as she travels across the country to discuss a variety of subjects with experts as well as regular people.
